wikipedia_page.main: Ailwyn Edward Fellowes, 3rd Baron de Ramsey KBE, TD (16 March 1910 – 31 March 1993) was a British peer and Territorial soldier.

link_mentions.page: Lord Lieutenant of Huntingdon and Peterborough

response: In 1951 the Ministry of Works made the gatehouse a Grade I listed building. In 1952 Ailwyn Fellowes, 3rd Baron de Ramsey gave the gatehouse to the National Trust in memory of his sister Diana Broughton.
*Ailwyn Fellowes, 3rd Baron de Ramsey, peer and Lord Lieutenant of Huntingdonshire

link_mentions.page: Ailwyn Edward Fellowes, 3rd Baron de Ramsey

response: His sister Lilah married Ailwyn Fellowes, 3rd Baron de Ramsey, a first cousin (once removed) of Winston Churchill.
* Ailwyn Fellowes, 3rd Baron de Ramsey was an officer in 336th Fd Bty throughout World War II, being taken prisoner at Singapore.Sainsbury, Hertfordshire Yeomanry.
